Steps For Building CMap Release
-------------------------------

-   Update the following files:
    * Changes
    * TODO
    * MANIFEST
    * README
    * INSTALL.pod
    * BUGS
    * docs/ADMINISTRATION.pod
    * docs/CODE_OVERVIEW.pod

-   Update SQL and docs:
    * Dump development db from MySQL with "mysqldump --no-data"
    * Convert to various formats with SQL::Translator:
        $ sqlt -f MySQL -t YAML dump.sql > dump.yml
        $ sqlt -f YAML -t MySQL dump.yml > sql/cmap.create.mysql
        $ sqlt -f YAML -t Oracle dump.yml > sql/cmap.create.oracle
        $ sqlt -f YAML -t PostgreSQL dump.yml > sql/cmap.create.postgresql
        $ sqlt -f YAML -t Sybase dump.yml > sql/cmap.create.sybase
        $ sqlt -f YAML -t SQLite dump.yml > sql/cmap.create.sqlite
        $ sqlt -f YAML -t HTML --title 'CMap Version' dump.yml > docs/cmap-schema-desc.html
        $ sqlt-diagram -d YAML --color --title 'CMap Version' dump.yml > docs/cmap-schema.png
        $ sqlt-graph -d YAML --color --height 7.5 --width 13 dump.yml > docs/cmap-schema-graph.png

-   Dump the data from a small sample database:
    $ mysqldump --no-create-info test > data/sample-dump.sql
    $ gzip !$
    (or use "sqlt-dumper" to make a dumper script)

-   Make sure "cmap.conf.PL" and "Constants.pm.PL" have the latest contents

-   Check with "./Build distcheck"

-   Create tarball with "./Build dist"

-   Test installation from tarball on a different machine
